"The European Commission has published its first report 1 on the implementation of the Data Protection Directive (95/46/EC). Under Article 33 of the latter, the Commission is required to make regular reports on progress to implementation at national level. Subsequent delays in this process by France, Germany, Ireland, Luxembourg and The Netherlands led to the postponement of the report until May 2003. Of these, France remains as the only one of the above not to have brought its existing data protection legislation into line with the current directive."
